b'Just my truest friends getting together to put on a show. The result may not be dazzling but the experience sure was...'

b'A decade on and I\xe2\x80\x99ve made 2 feature films, 70 episodes of TV, acted in other people\xe2\x80\x99s movies and been onstage at SNL and Carnegie Hall, all stuff that blew my mind and filled my soul. But this remains the most magical day of art making I\xe2\x80\x99ve had...'

b'There were cameos from @jerrysaltz and Woodrow Morton and Ariel Schulman and more. Everyone was so thrilled to be in this magical space with all the grownups gone. I was overwhelmed with both responsibility and gratitude, knowing it would always matter to us.'

b'We had a tiny crew, no budget but we did have the support of Rob Pruitt, the museum itself and our intrepid cinematographer Sara Rossein. We packed into the museum on a day it was closed and we brought every prop we could find in our parents\xe2\x80\x99 homes.'

b'My favorite museum in New York is the Guggenheim - spiritual space to so many. 10 years ago I had the chance to film there. It was part of a web series (remember those?) called Delusional Downtown Divas, made with my childhood friends @YoungIsabel & @joana_avillez'
